What is Groovy?
 - OOP
 - Uses Java Platform
 - Typings: Dynamic as well as static
 - Features similar to Python, Ruby
 - Super version of Java: provides DSL Support, Closures

 - test.groovy
 - gets compiled in Java Bytecode so it runs 
   on any platform with JRE installed

 - Meta Programming: getters/setters are auto generated


Features: 
 - List, Map, Range, Regular Expressions
 - Multithreading & Metaprogramming
 - no class declaration
 - can contain methods outside class defn
 - operator overloading
